{
  "stem": "210.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at that time they, took my father and my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they beat them up so much.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They held them for I don't know how many days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we went to the Jewish [ BACKROUND NOISE ] community, and, you know, to, you know, to-- and we-- I don't know how much money we had to give at that time to free my father and my-- my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because my brother [LAUGHS] you know, apparently beat up this little German boy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there is so many little incidents.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, like we had, where we used to live, the houses burned down.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Next door to us was a German-- German people that lived-- were our neighbors.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we always had wonderful relations with them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And sometimes I used to go there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they used to-- she used to give us food, you know, or she would bring sometimes things to our house.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But she was scared of her own children, that her children might turn her in-- that she's helping us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was just the most horrendous thing just to live from day to day.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] My son just came in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] And-- and at that time, when they-- we had to give all this money to bring my father.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, you know, through the, you know, there in the Jewish commentate, always had these [NON-ENGLISH], you know, like they talk to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they, you know, for a price, they-- so they told us we had to give them so much money.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know from where we took the money at that time, but somehow I think neighbors and everybody helped out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that took my father and my-- my grandfather back.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
